<item>
            <title>[LU-16509] quash memcpy WARN_ONCE false positives</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16509</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux v6.1-rc1-4-g6f7630b1b5bc&lt;br/&gt;
   fortify: Capture __bos() results in const temp var&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;__fortify_memcpy_chk&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; added a WARN_ONCE for runtime detection of detected field-spanning write.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This triggers with structs that have zero sized, or flexible array members (Typically data headers with sized payloads).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently lustre sizes and checks these objects appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
